What is Machine Language?

Machine language contains only

0

1

Example

10110010

11001011

11101001

CPU understands only this.

Why can't CPU understand C?

Because CPU is an electronic circuit.

It understands only

ON

OFF

Which are represented by

1

0
Step 5: Linker

Suppose you write

printf("Hello");

Did you write the code for printf()?

No.

It is already present inside the C Standard Library.

The linker finds that code and joins it with your program.

Without the linker,

printf() would not work.

Interview Question

Why do we need a linker?

Answer:

It combines your object code with required library code (like printf) to create an executable program.

Step 6: Executable File

After linking

You get

program.exe

(or no extension on Linux).

Now the program is ready to run.

Step 7: Loader

When you double-click

program.exe

The Loader

Loads the program into RAM.
Creates the memory layout (Text, Data, BSS, Heap, Stack).
Gives control to the CPU.
CPU Executes

Now

CPU starts executing instructions one by one.

